# Figma design (mandatory)

**Applies when** the user asks to make, create, update, polish, or fix a **design** (Figma screens, flows, mockups, cases, UI states, menus, icons in Figma, etc.). Ignore this rule for pure code/git work with no design ask.

1. **Read and follow** [`docs/figma-design.md`](docs/figma-design.md) **before** any Figma MCP / `use_figma` work.
2. Treat that doc as the project contract — do not invent alternate layout, button, or icon patterns.
3. After edits, run the checklist at the end of `docs/figma-design.md` (DS instances, no demo banners, phone size, note boxes, no frame-title clutter / white fills).

## Non-negotiables (summary)

- Reuse **Design System** components/icons (instance buttons, `Icon / run`, top bars) — never homemade `▶` or freehand buttons.
- Match **Projects management** / **Files editor** density; flow phones **240×420**.
- Design **real product** UI — no v0.1/demo banners on phones.
- In-progress = **•••** dots; complete = check; failed step = ✕ + clear error.
- Blank phone frame names; prefer rectangles + DS instances inside; notes in **boxes**.

